data.description: Nestled in a cul-de-sac and conveniently close, this home with three bedrooms, a bonus room, den, enclosed porch, and 2.5 baths has recently undergone a transformation, including the installation of a new water filtration system (just take a look at those fantastic cabinets). The property also features a finished den with a fireplace, an enclosed sunroom, extra sheds for storage, and a charming swing for embracing the tranquility of the surroundings. With stainless steel appliances, Corian countertops, a breakfast bar, and abundant storage, the kitchen is a standout. Additional highlights include spacious bookshelves, a newer roof, a recently remodeled bathroom, and newly added flooring.
